			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">In issue 3113 we added the FlattenGlobals pass which converts global variable initialisers into a flattened normal form.  We'd like to go further and simplify the pexe format so that each global variable initialiser is represented as an array of bytes + an array of relocations.

This will let us remove some baggage from the pexe format:

 * The top-level constants block (including ConstantExprs)
 * The more complex uses of the top-level types block (including struct types)

(This task is from the list at https://docs.google.com/document/d/1HvZJVwS9KeTc0jUvoQjbLapRbStHk3mZ0rPDUHNN96Y/edit.)
